  <p>I enjoy building full-stack applications, although I have a particular interest in frontend development becayse I love seeing ideas come to life. I'm always looking to expand my skills, with .NET currently high on the list of technologies I'd like to explore.</p>

  <p>Outside of programming I have a wide range of interests. I enjoy astronomy, gaming, robotics and history, and I like learning how things work. When I'm not at the computer, you'll often find me playing table tennis, badminton, swimming, golfing, reading, baking food or listening to music. I play a little ukulele and keyboard, enjoy drawing and even experimenting with composing music from time to time (though mostly for game projects).</p>

  <p>I am currently in Year 13 and am nowlooking to move directly into a software devlopment role. My focus is gaining real-world experience and continuing to grow through practical, project-based learning.</p>
